WEBVTT

00:06.960 --> 00:09.490
<i>Previously on</i>
Daisy Jones and The Six...

00:09.690 --> 00:11.200
What'd I miss?

00:11.400 --> 00:12.330
Who the fuck is this guy?

00:12.520 --> 00:13.910
Everybody, this is Nicky,

00:14.110 --> 00:15.720
- my husband.
- Hi.

00:16.970 --> 00:18.370
[snorts]

00:18.570 --> 00:19.870
<i>[Billy] It's gonna be a long</i>
<i>tour, so if you prefer</i>

00:20.070 --> 00:21.460
<i>to sit this one out,</i>
<i>please, be my guest.</i>

00:21.660 --> 00:22.540
<i>[Daisy] There's no tour</i>
<i>without me,</i>

00:22.740 --> 00:23.750
<i>you dumb son of a bitch.</i>

00:23.950 --> 00:24.800
Why aren't you playing

00:25.000 --> 00:26.340
"Look At Us Now" on this tour?

00:26.540 --> 00:27.970
Just needed to make room
for the new song...

00:28.170 --> 00:29.300
That's not the reason.

00:29.500 --> 00:30.720
What, you want me to believe
that that's real?

00:30.920 --> 00:31.890
<i>That you're happy,</i>
<i>and you're in love?</i>

00:32.090 --> 00:32.890
<i>[Daisy] I am happy!</i>

00:33.090 --> 00:34.060
<i>And I am in love.</i>

00:34.250 --> 00:35.600
<i>[Billy] I know</i>
<i>what it looks like</i>

00:35.800 --> 00:37.160
<i>when you're in love</i>
<i>with someone.</i>

00:38.830 --> 00:40.230
<i>[Camila] I was confused,</i>

00:40.430 --> 00:41.690
<i>and I was hurt,</i>

00:41.890 --> 00:43.060
<i>and you were there for me.</i>

00:43.260 --> 00:44.570
It's just never
gonna happen again.

00:44.770 --> 00:45.730
<i>[Karen] We've been screwing</i>

00:45.930 --> 00:47.650
<i>since the album sessions.</i>

00:47.850 --> 00:49.570
You guys have just been
too up your own asses to notice.

00:49.770 --> 00:51.410
<i>[Billy] She's never taken</i>
<i>this much before.</i>

00:51.610 --> 00:52.670
[snorts]

00:53.670 --> 00:55.790
<i>You can't tell me you don't</i>
<i>see it. She's tripping on stage,</i>

00:55.980 --> 00:57.450
<i>she's mixing up the lyrics.</i>

00:57.650 --> 00:59.040
Daisy.

00:59.240 --> 01:00.540
Daisy?

01:00.740 --> 01:01.870
Daisy.

01:02.070 --> 01:03.680
I can't be here.

01:07.860 --> 01:10.680
[long exhale]

01:10.870 --> 01:12.820
[♪ Fleetwood Mac:
"Gold Dust Woman"]

01:19.580 --> 01:20.890
Hi.

01:21.090 --> 01:22.900
♪ <i>Rock on, Gold Dust Woman...</i>

01:23.100 --> 01:24.110
Did I wake you?

01:24.300 --> 01:26.690
♪ <i>Take your silver spoon...</i>

01:26.890 --> 01:28.940
[Daisy] What happened?

01:29.140 --> 01:29.940
[sighs]

01:30.140 --> 01:31.950
You... you had a bit of fun,

01:32.150 --> 01:33.320
maybe too much.

01:33.520 --> 01:36.280
Hey, but you're okay now.

01:36.480 --> 01:38.660
I'm gonna call
for some breakfast, all right?

01:38.860 --> 01:40.910
♪ <i>Heartless challenge</i> ♪

01:41.110 --> 01:43.600
♪ <i>Pick your path</i>
<i>and I'll pray...</i>

01:48.310 --> 01:49.550
[Nicky] Hi. Hello. Hi.

01:49.750 --> 01:52.010
Could we order some breakfast,
please? Thank you.

01:52.210 --> 01:54.510
Yes, that's right. Yes.

01:54.710 --> 01:56.430
♪ <i>In the morning...</i>

01:56.630 --> 01:58.680
[Nicky] Yeah, sure.

01:58.880 --> 02:01.270
♪ <i>Loves to go down...</i>

02:01.470 --> 02:04.080
- Uh... Hang on. Daisy.
- [door opens]

02:06.750 --> 02:09.360
Daisy. Daisy, where you going?

02:09.560 --> 02:12.240
Daisy, you should be in bed.
Come on. Come back in.

02:12.440 --> 02:14.990
- Daisy. Daisy!
- [door slams]

02:15.190 --> 02:16.950
[banging on door]

02:17.150 --> 02:18.830
- [Nicky] Daisy.
- You okay?

02:19.030 --> 02:20.830
I need you to tell me
what happened.

02:21.030 --> 02:22.250
- Uh...
- [Nicky] Daisy, please.

02:22.450 --> 02:23.960
[doorknob jiggles]

02:24.160 --> 02:25.290
How much do you remember?

02:25.490 --> 02:27.130
I remember that you were there.

02:27.330 --> 02:29.140
Daisy, open the fucking door!

02:31.770 --> 02:33.300
Daisy, please.

02:33.500 --> 02:37.300
Rod called a doctor, and he...

02:37.500 --> 02:39.350
he got the drugs
out of your system.

02:39.550 --> 02:42.060
We left. I-I didn't think you'd
want me there when you woke up.

02:42.260 --> 02:44.100
And where

02:44.300 --> 02:47.330
was he the whole time?

02:51.830 --> 02:53.950
- Pack your shit up.
- [door slams]

02:54.140 --> 02:55.530
Daisy.

02:55.730 --> 02:57.280
Daisy, you wouldn't listen,
okay? I didn't know what to do.

02:57.480 --> 02:59.620
You left me
in the fucking shower?!

02:59.820 --> 03:02.250
- [door opens]
- [scoffs]

03:02.440 --> 03:03.790
Daisy...

03:03.990 --> 03:05.330
[Daisy] I said pack your shit up

03:05.530 --> 03:07.880
and get out of here!

03:08.080 --> 03:09.540
No.

03:09.740 --> 03:12.050
- [scoffs]
- Daisy...

03:12.250 --> 03:13.050
Daisy.

03:13.250 --> 03:14.650
[vase shatters]

03:17.570 --> 03:18.970
Whoa, whoa.

03:19.170 --> 03:20.810
[Warren] You heard the lady.

03:21.000 --> 03:22.850
- You heard her.
- [Nicky] You're making a huge

03:23.050 --> 03:24.140
fucking mistake.

03:24.340 --> 03:26.560
♪ <i>Well, did she make you cry</i> ♪

03:26.760 --> 03:28.650
♪ <i>Make you break down</i> ♪

03:28.850 --> 03:30.440
♪ <i>Shatter your illusions</i>
<i>of love?</i> ♪

03:30.640 --> 03:32.280
You'll regret this.

03:32.470 --> 03:33.690
♪ <i>And is it over now</i> ♪

03:33.890 --> 03:36.450
♪ <i>Do you know how?</i> ♪

03:36.650 --> 03:38.030
♪ <i>Pick up the pieces</i> ♪

03:38.230 --> 03:39.740
♪ <i>And go home</i> ♪

03:39.940 --> 03:42.120
♪ <i>Well, did she make you cry</i> ♪

03:42.320 --> 03:44.160
♪ <i>Make you break down</i> ♪

03:44.360 --> 03:46.660
♪ <i>Shatter your illusions</i>
<i>of love?</i> ♪

03:46.860 --> 03:49.880
♪ <i>And now tell me</i>
<i>is it over now</i> ♪

03:50.080 --> 03:52.040
♪ <i>Do you know how?</i> ♪♪

03:52.240 --> 03:55.670
[♪ Patti Smith:
"Dancing Barefoot"]

03:55.870 --> 03:58.050
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

03:58.250 --> 04:00.140
♪ <i>Is benediction</i> ♪

04:00.340 --> 04:02.310
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

04:02.500 --> 04:04.350
♪ <i>Is addicted to thee</i> ♪

04:04.550 --> 04:06.520
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

04:06.720 --> 04:08.600
♪ <i>Is the root connection</i> ♪

04:08.800 --> 04:10.730
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

04:10.930 --> 04:12.820
♪ <i>Is connecting with he</i> ♪

04:13.020 --> 04:14.980
♪ <i>Here I go</i> ♪

04:15.180 --> 04:18.610
♪ <i>And I don't know why</i> ♪

04:18.810 --> 04:21.660
♪ <i>I fell so ceaselessly</i> ♪

04:21.860 --> 04:24.660
♪ <i>Could it be he's taking</i> ♪

04:24.860 --> 04:27.810
♪ <i>Over me</i> ♪

04:30.220 --> 04:34.170
♪ <i>I'm dancing barefoot</i> ♪

04:34.370 --> 04:38.220
♪ <i>Heading for a spin</i> ♪

04:38.420 --> 04:41.260
♪ <i>Some strange music</i> ♪

04:41.460 --> 04:42.760
♪ <i>Draws me in</i> ♪

04:42.960 --> 04:44.260
♪ <i>Makes me come on</i> ♪

04:44.460 --> 04:46.990
♪ <i>Like some heroine</i> ♪♪

05:00.920 --> 05:02.920
[indistinct chatter]

05:06.760 --> 05:09.540
<i>[Daisy] You start</i>
<i>doing drugs to escape</i>

05:09.740 --> 05:12.830
<i>and to dull your emotions,</i>

05:13.030 --> 05:15.000
<i>but drugs don't dull</i>
<i>your emotions,</i>

05:15.200 --> 05:17.090
<i>they heighten them.</i>

05:17.290 --> 05:21.090
So, coming down is a lot like
rediscovering your sanity.

05:21.290 --> 05:23.430
[crowd cheering]

05:23.630 --> 05:26.010
<i>[Daisy] And when you</i>
<i>rediscover your sanity,</i>

05:26.210 --> 05:28.640
<i>it's only a matter of time</i>
<i>before you remember</i>

05:28.840 --> 05:30.850
<i>what it was you needed to escape</i>
<i>from in the first place.</i>

05:31.050 --> 05:33.230
Daisy! Autograph! Daisy!

05:33.430 --> 05:35.480
[fans screaming]

05:35.680 --> 05:36.690
Fucking bitch!

05:36.890 --> 05:39.150
[fan] Love you guys!

05:39.350 --> 05:41.360
Whoo!

05:41.560 --> 05:44.280
♪ <i>Every story has an ending</i> ♪

05:44.480 --> 05:48.910
♪ <i>And it's not our job to stay</i> ♪

05:49.110 --> 05:52.620
♪ <i>Now, how about</i>
<i>we turn it off?</i> ♪

05:52.820 --> 05:55.960
♪ <i>We'll forget it</i>
<i>like it's gone...</i>

05:56.160 --> 06:00.340
<i>[Karen] Even in shambles,</i>
<i>Daisy was a powerhouse,</i>

06:00.540 --> 06:02.900
<i>but this was just...</i>

06:04.400 --> 06:06.260
...sad.

06:06.460 --> 06:07.930
<i>[Daisy] Pick up, Simone.</i>

06:08.130 --> 06:09.640
[line ringing]

06:09.840 --> 06:13.390
♪ <i>You were gone, you were gone</i> ♪

06:13.590 --> 06:16.540
♪ <i>You were gone</i> ♪

06:27.340 --> 06:29.240
[knock on door]

06:29.440 --> 06:30.430
[door opens]

06:32.470 --> 06:33.410
Hi.

06:33.610 --> 06:35.370
- [TV clicks off]
- [door closes]

06:35.570 --> 06:37.540
I can't be on that bus anymore.

06:37.740 --> 06:39.850
[indistinct chatter
and laughter outside]

06:50.990 --> 06:52.930
I've wanted this life

06:53.130 --> 06:54.980
since I was

06:55.180 --> 06:57.480
14 years old.

06:57.680 --> 06:59.520
Yeah, me, too.

06:59.720 --> 07:03.960
[Daisy] So why
are we so unhappy?

07:08.090 --> 07:10.700
I don't know.

07:10.900 --> 07:12.750
[Daisy] I don't either.

07:12.940 --> 07:16.000
And that...

07:16.200 --> 07:18.380
that just makes it worse.

07:18.580 --> 07:20.710
And you make it worse.

07:20.910 --> 07:22.050
How do I make it worse?

07:22.250 --> 07:25.050
Because you were right,

07:25.250 --> 07:27.650
and I hate that.

07:29.360 --> 07:32.720
I hate

07:32.920 --> 07:35.330
that you saw me like that.

07:37.910 --> 07:40.770
And I hate

07:40.970 --> 07:43.500
that you were the one
who saved me.

07:49.920 --> 07:53.240
I've been there, too, remember?

07:53.440 --> 07:55.600
Why don't you call Teddy?

07:59.770 --> 08:02.800
You know I'd take you, right?

08:02.990 --> 08:05.190
If you ever wanted to go.

08:08.190 --> 08:10.900
- [glass shatters]
- [laughter outside]

08:13.360 --> 08:15.820
Can I sleep here tonight?

08:20.290 --> 08:22.790
Of course. I'll, uh...

08:40.970 --> 08:43.670
So, wait, wait, wait,
he was just gonna, what,

08:43.870 --> 08:45.710
[scoffs] leave her there?

08:45.910 --> 08:47.210
<i>[Billy over phone] I guess.</i>

08:47.410 --> 08:49.340
<i>[Camila] That's awful.</i>
<i>Poor Daisy.</i>

08:49.540 --> 08:51.070
<i>Is she okay?</i>

08:52.820 --> 08:54.310
She's Daisy, so...

08:54.500 --> 08:57.770
<i>[interviewer] How did it feel</i>
<i>to be sober on tour?</i>

08:57.970 --> 09:00.600
<i>[Daisy] "Sober" isn't</i>
<i>the right word for it, no.</i>

09:00.800 --> 09:02.400
<i>What I did was...</i>

09:02.600 --> 09:04.650
<i>I started making rules</i>
<i>for myself.</i>

09:04.850 --> 09:06.360
No dexies in the morning.

09:06.560 --> 09:08.360
A bump of coke,
but only before shows.

09:08.560 --> 09:12.320
<i>A quaalude at night</i>
<i>to bring me down.</i>

09:12.520 --> 09:14.370
<i>It was the best that I could do,</i>

09:14.570 --> 09:16.260
under the circumstances.

09:21.430 --> 09:23.430
[crowd cheering]

09:27.940 --> 09:29.260
You need a rest.

09:29.460 --> 09:30.820
Take it.

09:37.530 --> 09:39.120
[fan 1] Marry me, Daisy! Whoo!

09:44.750 --> 09:47.040
I almost died the other night.

09:49.840 --> 09:52.700
[fan 2] We love you, Daisy!

09:52.900 --> 09:55.030
[fan 3] Daisy!

09:55.230 --> 09:58.200
I was this close.

09:58.400 --> 10:01.010
[fan 4] Daisy, I love you!

10:03.390 --> 10:06.500
[fan 5] Daisy!

10:06.700 --> 10:08.630
But I'm alive tonight.

10:08.830 --> 10:12.380
[crowd cheering]

10:12.580 --> 10:15.030
And you're alive tonight.

10:19.870 --> 10:23.350
So, let's just stay alive
a little bit longer.

10:23.550 --> 10:25.500
[drums playing]

10:28.000 --> 10:29.780
[band playing]

10:29.970 --> 10:32.590
[overlapping chatter]

10:33.840 --> 10:35.860
- Pyrotechnics.
- Excuse me?

10:36.060 --> 10:38.580
You guys are selling out
15,000-seaters now.

10:38.780 --> 10:39.870
- [laughs]
- Don't you think it's time

10:40.070 --> 10:42.450
to add a little fire,
a little scope?

10:42.650 --> 10:45.080
You know, Rod,
don't overthink it.

10:45.280 --> 10:47.230
I'm the fire.

10:51.150 --> 10:52.860
She's back.

10:54.570 --> 10:57.390
Spring '77.

10:57.590 --> 10:59.010
This was our moment.

10:59.210 --> 11:02.060
It's when you least
want things to change

11:02.260 --> 11:04.310
that they always do.

11:04.510 --> 11:06.080
[band playing punk rock]

11:08.370 --> 11:11.290
[singing indistinctly]

11:12.710 --> 11:15.360
It's over.

11:15.560 --> 11:17.450
Why would anybody care about us
when stuff like this exists?

11:17.650 --> 11:19.070
We're done, man,

11:19.270 --> 11:20.740
- we're dinosaurs.
- [Karen] What're you
talking about?

11:20.940 --> 11:22.830
Don't worry so much.

11:23.030 --> 11:24.620
Mm.

11:24.820 --> 11:27.250
What is this shit?

11:27.450 --> 11:29.290
The future.

11:29.490 --> 11:33.020
Yeah? [stammers]
I'll be right back.

11:36.190 --> 11:38.340
You remember playing
rooms this size?

11:38.540 --> 11:41.510
- Yeah.
- I kind of miss it.

11:41.710 --> 11:43.720
Me, too.

11:43.920 --> 11:46.980
- [man 1] Fuck yeah!
- [crowd cheering]

11:47.180 --> 11:48.810
[man 2] Fuck you, motherfucker!

11:49.010 --> 11:51.150
Oh, hey, man. [chuckles]

11:51.350 --> 11:52.570
I'm, uh,

11:52.770 --> 11:55.440
I'm in a band, too. Uh, The Six.

11:55.640 --> 11:57.320
I mean,

11:57.520 --> 11:58.660
you probably don't listen
to the radio.

11:58.860 --> 12:00.990
I've-I've heard you. My, uh,

12:01.190 --> 12:04.500
my little sister plays
your record all the time.

12:04.690 --> 12:07.870
[indistinct chatter]

12:08.070 --> 12:10.290
[♪ Toto: "Hold the Line"]

12:10.490 --> 12:12.500
<i>[Warren] We had the biggest</i>
<i>album in the country.</i>

12:12.700 --> 12:16.550
We were nominated for a whole
bunch of fucking Grammys.

12:16.750 --> 12:19.590
We were on
<i>Saturday Night Live.</i> I mean...

12:19.790 --> 12:22.650
It's called a "moment"
for a reason, though, right?

12:27.530 --> 12:28.890
[crowd cheering]

12:29.090 --> 12:31.560
♪ <i>It's not in the way</i>
<i>that you hold me</i> ♪

12:31.760 --> 12:33.690
[fan] I love you!

12:33.890 --> 12:35.900
♪ <i>It's not in the way</i>
<i>you say you care...</i>

12:36.100 --> 12:37.150
[fans screaming]

12:37.350 --> 12:39.150
[mom] Daisy, Daisy. My daughter

12:39.350 --> 12:41.740
wants to be you
when she grows up. [chuckles]

12:41.940 --> 12:45.240
Dream bigger, little bird.

12:45.440 --> 12:47.500
You can be anything
you want to be.

12:47.700 --> 12:50.080
♪ <i>It's not in the way you...</i>

12:50.280 --> 12:51.960
[laughs] Thanks.

12:52.160 --> 12:54.090
♪ <i>Hold the line...</i>

12:54.290 --> 12:55.800
All right.

12:56.000 --> 12:59.590
♪ <i>Love isn't always on time...</i>

12:59.790 --> 13:02.640
Hey, look at this guy.

13:02.840 --> 13:04.560
- Hey. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

13:04.750 --> 13:05.970
Rod didn't tell you
I was coming?

13:06.170 --> 13:07.350
He did, but we didn't think
you'd show up.

13:07.550 --> 13:08.390
Hey, come on now, you know

13:08.590 --> 13:09.890
I wouldn't miss this
for the world.

13:10.090 --> 13:11.600
- Gonna go get ready, all right?
- [chuckles]

13:11.800 --> 13:13.690
Simone, is she with you?

13:13.890 --> 13:15.110
No.

13:15.310 --> 13:16.820
Oh, I told her I'd meet her
for a drink,

13:17.020 --> 13:18.490
but I just figured I'd catch up
with her here first.

13:18.690 --> 13:20.780
You know, I don't know.
I'll see you in a minute.

13:20.980 --> 13:23.530
♪ <i>Oh, oh</i> ♪

13:23.730 --> 13:25.740
♪ <i>It's not in the way</i>
<i>that you...</i>

13:25.940 --> 13:28.330
Shit, shit, shit, shit.

13:28.530 --> 13:30.680
- Hey, Daisy.
- Shit, shit, shit, shit.

13:32.310 --> 13:33.290
- Daisy.
- I'm sorry.

13:33.490 --> 13:34.880
I can't find my fucking pills,

13:35.080 --> 13:36.040
and I-I can't...

13:36.240 --> 13:37.420
- It's okay.
- It's not okay.

13:37.620 --> 13:38.670
Everything feels too real.

13:38.870 --> 13:41.780
I-I can't do it.

13:43.240 --> 13:44.640
<i>[stage manager] And</i>
<i>we're live in six...</i>

13:44.840 --> 13:47.530
five... four...

13:51.240 --> 13:54.100
Ladies and gentlemen,
my new favorite band,

13:54.300 --> 13:55.940
Daisy Jones and The Six.

13:56.140 --> 13:57.920
[audience cheering]

14:06.760 --> 14:10.350
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

14:12.930 --> 14:15.060
[♪ "Aurora"]

14:22.770 --> 14:25.430
♪ <i>You found me in flames</i> ♪

14:25.630 --> 14:29.220
♪ <i>It's the daylight of change</i> ♪

14:29.420 --> 14:32.680
♪ <i>And all that stuff is done</i> ♪

14:32.880 --> 14:35.730
♪ <i>You're my morning sun</i> ♪

14:35.930 --> 14:38.820
♪ <i>Aurora you're the one</i> ♪

14:39.020 --> 14:42.070
♪ <i>You're my morning sun</i> ♪

14:42.270 --> 14:45.050
♪ <i>Aurora you're the one</i> ♪

14:49.550 --> 14:52.700
- ♪ <i>And where did you turn</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Where did you turn</i> ♪

14:52.900 --> 14:55.620
- ♪ <i>When you needed tenderness</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>When you needed tenderness</i> ♪

14:55.820 --> 14:57.330
♪ <i>When you reached out</i>
<i>for my touch</i> ♪

14:57.530 --> 14:58.960
♪ <i>When you reached</i>
<i>out for my touch</i> ♪

14:59.160 --> 15:02.170
♪ <i>And I couldn't</i>
<i>give you much of all...</i>

15:02.370 --> 15:03.170
[knock on door]

15:03.370 --> 15:05.690
Hot off the presses.

15:07.490 --> 15:08.890
- [chuckles]
- Wanted to bring it to you

15:09.090 --> 15:10.860
soon as I got it.
I'm sorry it took so long.

15:12.450 --> 15:15.020
You kidding me? I've been
waiting my whole life for this.

15:15.220 --> 15:17.830
Well, then Attic Records
is lucky to have you.

15:22.960 --> 15:25.900
There's just one thing that's...

15:26.100 --> 15:27.110
Well,

15:27.310 --> 15:29.550
we should talk about it.

15:33.010 --> 15:36.710
♪ <i>I kind of thought that night</i>
<i>was gonna last forever</i> ♪

15:36.910 --> 15:39.500
♪ <i>Kind of thought</i>
<i>that night was gonna last</i> ♪

15:39.700 --> 15:42.340
♪ <i>Forever, kind of thought</i>
<i>that night was gonna</i> ♪

15:42.540 --> 15:46.220
♪ <i>Last forever, kind of thought</i>
<i>that night was gonna</i> ♪

15:46.420 --> 15:49.150
♪ <i>Last forever,</i>
<i>kind of thought</i> ♪

16:04.130 --> 16:05.190
[song ends]

16:05.390 --> 16:08.250
[audience cheering]

16:17.100 --> 16:19.120
Look, it's not a problem.

16:19.320 --> 16:20.500
What isn't?

16:20.700 --> 16:22.500
They don't want any rumors.

16:22.700 --> 16:24.380
But they're not rumors.

16:24.580 --> 16:26.800
Come on, Bernie, you know
what I mean. It's...

16:27.000 --> 16:28.650
[sighs]

16:30.900 --> 16:32.680
Look.

16:32.880 --> 16:36.350
I promise this is not
gonna change anything.

16:36.550 --> 16:39.520
- Of course it is.
- We're...

16:39.720 --> 16:42.650
They won't want me going
on the road with you.

16:42.850 --> 16:45.030
They're not gonna want me
anywhere near you.

16:45.220 --> 16:46.990
I'm not gonna let that happen.
They can't...

16:47.190 --> 16:49.450
You won't have a choice.

16:49.650 --> 16:53.780
Right now, this is when
you have the choice.

16:53.980 --> 16:55.930
Tell them to go to hell.

16:59.060 --> 17:00.750
[scoffs]

17:00.950 --> 17:02.540
What?

17:02.740 --> 17:04.750
This is what
I've been working for.

17:04.950 --> 17:07.610
Bernie, this is what
I've always wanted.

17:09.270 --> 17:11.900
And here I thought I was.

17:16.870 --> 17:18.810
- Hey.
- Good job, you guys.

17:19.010 --> 17:21.140
[laughs] You're always
something else.

17:21.340 --> 17:25.250
- Um, listen,
I'll be right back.
- All right.

17:29.340 --> 17:32.660
Hey. You were amazing tonight.

17:32.860 --> 17:34.530
- [laughs] Why, thank you.
- [laughs]

17:34.730 --> 17:36.240
- So natural.
- You, too.

17:36.440 --> 17:38.540
- So funny. Yeah.
- Thanks.

17:38.740 --> 17:40.330
Um...

17:40.530 --> 17:43.080
You know, um...

17:43.280 --> 17:46.170
You know, a lot of guys are
intimidated by funny women.

17:46.370 --> 17:49.050
- Are they?
- Oh, yeah. Big-time, big-time.

17:49.250 --> 17:51.630
But, uh, you know, not me.

17:51.830 --> 17:53.260
I think it's
pretty hot actually.

17:53.460 --> 17:56.560
It's a real, uh,
it's a real turn-on.

17:56.750 --> 18:00.100
You know what's
a real turn-on for me?

18:00.300 --> 18:01.940
No. I don't know.

18:02.130 --> 18:04.410
Drummers in rock bands.

18:05.660 --> 18:08.900
[laughs]

18:09.100 --> 18:11.990
That's-that's exactly
what I'm talking about.

18:12.190 --> 18:13.130
[laughing]

18:16.340 --> 18:17.830
Are you serious?

18:18.030 --> 18:19.910
How'd it feel?

18:20.110 --> 18:21.460
- It felt good.
- Yeah?

18:21.650 --> 18:23.710
Yeah. I mean,
not as good as cocaine.

18:23.910 --> 18:25.580
- [woman 1] Someone help!
- [woman 2] We need a medic!

18:25.780 --> 18:27.130
[man] Call an ambulance.

18:27.330 --> 18:29.090
[siren wailing]

18:29.290 --> 18:31.230
[crowd shouting]

18:36.240 --> 18:39.160
Everyone back, everyone back.
Come on, let them through.

18:42.080 --> 18:44.830
[security guard] Back up, man.
Hey, I said back it up.

18:53.130 --> 18:55.860
There was a blockage
in the blood flow to his heart.

18:56.060 --> 18:57.160
What does that mean?

18:57.360 --> 18:59.330
It means we might not know
the extent

18:59.530 --> 19:00.950
of the damage for a while, but

19:01.150 --> 19:02.580
he's stable.

19:02.780 --> 19:05.010
Okay. Thank you.

19:13.060 --> 19:15.570
I could really use
a drink right now.

19:21.780 --> 19:24.120
You think things happen
for a reason?

19:26.660 --> 19:28.370
I don't know.

19:31.040 --> 19:33.940
Do you?

19:34.140 --> 19:35.070
I used to.

19:35.270 --> 19:37.030
I used to believe in everything,

19:37.230 --> 19:39.950
in God and angels and heaven

19:40.150 --> 19:44.290
and somebody up there
looking down on us.

19:44.490 --> 19:46.710
But that night in Miami,

19:46.910 --> 19:51.210
I swear I died for a moment,
and there was nothing there.

19:51.410 --> 19:54.190
Not a goddamn thing.

19:56.520 --> 19:59.640
So, now I don't know.

19:59.840 --> 20:02.310
Wow, Daisy, you're really
cheering me up.

20:02.510 --> 20:03.720
- Thank you.
- Well, I'm just telling

20:03.920 --> 20:05.280
the truth.

20:07.080 --> 20:09.950
So, how do you explain us?

20:11.960 --> 20:13.150
I mean, I should've been dead

20:13.350 --> 20:15.990
long before now.

20:16.190 --> 20:18.700
Killed in action like
half the kids in my high school.

20:18.900 --> 20:21.030
Or maybe drinking myself
to death back in Hazelwood,

20:21.230 --> 20:23.970
like my old man.

20:25.640 --> 20:28.080
But that's not
what happened, is it?

20:28.280 --> 20:32.390
What happened is I started
playing in a band.

20:33.440 --> 20:35.130
I met Teddy Price

20:35.330 --> 20:37.320
buying cigarettes
in a Hollywood market.

20:43.610 --> 20:46.430
And then I met you.

20:46.630 --> 20:49.120
And here we are...

20:52.290 --> 20:55.610
...in this place

20:55.810 --> 20:57.280
with this life.

20:57.480 --> 20:59.570
You're telling me
there's no one up there

20:59.770 --> 21:01.880
looking out for us?

21:03.470 --> 21:05.130
Come on.

21:08.680 --> 21:11.600
Hey, guys, he's awake.

21:14.100 --> 21:16.130
- Can we see him?
- One at a time.

21:16.330 --> 21:17.560
You go.

21:27.410 --> 21:28.890
But it's on you, too,
Mr. Price.

21:29.090 --> 21:30.730
You need to take care
of yourself.

21:30.930 --> 21:33.310
So no more smoking,
no more drugs.

21:33.510 --> 21:35.150
Cut back on the red meat
and alcohol.

21:35.350 --> 21:37.030
What about work?

21:37.220 --> 21:40.550
- Depends. How stressful is
your work environment?
- [Billy scoffs]

21:43.260 --> 21:47.010
- You won't survive
another one of these.
- I understand.

21:49.010 --> 21:51.560
- Thanks, Doc.
- Mm-hmm.

22:01.230 --> 22:03.550
I love you, Teddy.

22:03.750 --> 22:06.760
I owe everything to you.

22:06.960 --> 22:09.810
If you died, I can't...

22:10.010 --> 22:13.560
I don't know what I'd do.

22:13.760 --> 22:15.770
I'm not gonna die, son.

22:15.970 --> 22:17.870
No, not yet.

22:18.920 --> 22:21.400
But when I do,

22:21.600 --> 22:24.490
you definitely are not speaking
at my funeral.

22:24.690 --> 22:26.240
[Teddy laughs]

22:26.440 --> 22:29.740
[coughing]

22:29.940 --> 22:32.330
Just promise me you'll
take it easy, all right?

22:32.530 --> 22:36.040
No more burning the candle
at both ends.

22:36.240 --> 22:39.690
Teddy, if it kills you...

22:41.560 --> 22:44.110
Then I die on top
of the world.

22:51.240 --> 22:53.240
♪ ♪

23:01.420 --> 23:04.320
- Is he okay?
- He's okay.

23:04.520 --> 23:06.300
Okay. Okay.

23:08.510 --> 23:11.160
It was Teddy who noticed me,

23:11.360 --> 23:14.620
took me under his wing.

23:14.820 --> 23:17.060
Gave me my shot.

23:19.850 --> 23:23.190
I just thank God
he's gonna be okay.

23:26.320 --> 23:28.890
I want us to be okay.

23:29.090 --> 23:31.820
[sirens passing]

23:35.330 --> 23:39.110
What I said was so awful.

23:39.310 --> 23:40.480
And I'm so sorry.

23:40.680 --> 23:42.210
Daisy...

23:52.760 --> 23:55.250
[Daisy crying softly]

23:55.450 --> 23:59.210
I remember after that
a sense of calm.

23:59.410 --> 24:01.350
[cheering]

24:06.820 --> 24:08.090
<i>[Karen] The usual band stuff.</i>

24:08.290 --> 24:10.220
Nothing really out
of the ordinary.

24:10.420 --> 24:13.260
Other than Warren dating
a movie star.

24:13.460 --> 24:15.890
I was dating a movie star.

24:16.090 --> 24:17.770
<i>[Daisy] And Billy and I were...</i>

24:17.970 --> 24:21.400
<i>Well, we were never</i>
<i>just one thing.</i>

24:21.600 --> 24:23.480
<i>But for the first time,</i>
<i>I think I could imagine</i>

24:23.680 --> 24:26.070
a version of us that might last.

24:26.270 --> 24:27.460
[order bell dings]

24:29.260 --> 24:32.830
[laughter]

24:33.030 --> 24:34.790
Oh, man. Oh, thank you.

24:34.990 --> 24:36.250
Thank you.

24:36.450 --> 24:38.850
Wait, I know you
from somewhere.

24:41.810 --> 24:44.670
No way. Well, hey,

24:44.870 --> 24:46.130
as long as you're
in my section,

24:46.330 --> 24:48.550
no one will bother you.
You have my word.

24:48.750 --> 24:51.140
- Thank you very much.
- [Daisy chuckles]

24:51.340 --> 24:53.850
Crazy.

24:54.050 --> 24:55.990
It's only gonna get worse
with the next album.

24:58.370 --> 25:00.200
You've been thinking
about it?

25:01.250 --> 25:03.860
I mean, yeah, sure,
I've been thinking about it.

25:04.060 --> 25:06.710
Well, you written anything?

25:09.000 --> 25:11.300
Yeah, me neither.
Not really.

25:14.630 --> 25:16.540
There is one song
that I, um...

25:16.740 --> 25:18.250
Check, please.

25:18.450 --> 25:20.040
We're gonna miss sound check.

25:20.240 --> 25:23.330
Ah, Billy can play my part.

25:23.530 --> 25:26.340
Like he ever could.

25:26.540 --> 25:29.520
God, I love it when
you say stuff like that.

25:40.030 --> 25:42.040
[door closes]

25:51.000 --> 25:52.280
[♪ "It Was Always You"]

25:52.480 --> 25:54.490
♪ <i>Got a live one</i>
<i>warned his friends</i> ♪

25:54.690 --> 25:58.040
♪ <i>This is not a faith</i>
<i>to awaken</i> ♪

25:58.240 --> 26:01.540
♪ <i>Their love will never live</i>
<i>they always said</i> ♪

26:01.740 --> 26:04.960
♪ <i>To see the toll</i>
<i>it could have taken</i> ♪

26:05.160 --> 26:07.670
♪ <i>Like I could forget my name</i> ♪

26:07.870 --> 26:09.940
♪ <i>I swore I'd never</i>
<i>darken your door</i> ♪

26:11.570 --> 26:14.050
♪ <i>You'll say it was insane</i> ♪

26:14.250 --> 26:18.010
♪ <i>We never could go back</i>
<i>to before</i> ♪

26:18.210 --> 26:21.680
♪ <i>I didn't know it</i> ♪

26:21.880 --> 26:25.450
♪ <i>I can't control it</i> ♪

26:28.870 --> 26:33.840
♪ <i>It was always you</i> ♪

26:35.420 --> 26:42.080
♪ <i>It was always you</i> ♪

26:42.280 --> 26:48.630
♪ <i>I was always true</i> ♪

26:48.830 --> 26:54.320
♪ <i>It was always you</i> ♪♪

26:57.490 --> 27:00.680
- That was a bit of a mess.
- Daisy...

27:00.880 --> 27:03.490
Hey.

27:07.870 --> 27:08.980
<i>[interviewer] Can you talk about</i>

27:09.180 --> 27:12.610
what happened in Boston?

27:12.810 --> 27:16.340
Did Karen... Karen tell you?

27:18.170 --> 27:21.330
It's not my place
to say anything, really.

27:21.530 --> 27:23.260
[interviewer] She told me.

27:27.930 --> 27:29.640
I need some water.

27:32.690 --> 27:34.170
Oh, my God.

27:34.370 --> 27:37.760
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

27:37.960 --> 27:39.430
Graham, please.

27:39.630 --> 27:40.600
I'm sorry, I don't...

27:40.800 --> 27:42.220
I don't think I've ever
been this happy.

27:42.420 --> 27:45.440
- Graham, please stop.
- Hey, what's wrong?

27:45.630 --> 27:47.290
What's the matter?

27:50.250 --> 27:52.750
- We can make this work.
- How?

27:54.040 --> 27:58.030
I don't know,
but we figure it out, right?

27:58.230 --> 28:00.030
I mean, we-we get
a new keyboardist...

28:00.230 --> 28:01.630
Excuse me?

28:02.840 --> 28:05.620
I'm not quitting the band
to raise a baby.

28:05.820 --> 28:07.140
Are you?

28:08.180 --> 28:09.810
No. I'm sorry. That's...

28:11.600 --> 28:13.380
I didn't...

28:13.580 --> 28:16.170
I never wanted this, Graham.
You know that.

28:16.370 --> 28:19.010
Karen, you didn't want
this either?

28:19.210 --> 28:22.310
Can we take some time?

28:22.500 --> 28:24.410
Think about it?

28:27.740 --> 28:30.270
The next day we went home.

28:30.470 --> 28:35.110
Fucking Pittsburgh.

28:35.310 --> 28:37.250
[cheering]

28:38.550 --> 28:40.760
[fans whooping, screaming]

28:45.930 --> 28:47.410
[fan] Pittsburgh loves you!

28:47.610 --> 28:49.430
[cheering continues]

28:50.470 --> 28:53.210
- Hey.
- Oh, my baby.

28:53.410 --> 28:54.850
Grandma.

28:57.110 --> 28:58.820
- This is Karen.
- Oh...

29:00.820 --> 29:03.430
Daddy.

29:03.630 --> 29:06.870
[fan] Daisy Jones, I love you!

29:09.740 --> 29:12.480
Daisy Jones.

29:12.680 --> 29:15.040
Mrs. Dunne.

29:16.040 --> 29:17.080
Oh!

29:19.170 --> 29:21.030
[♪ Earth, Wind & Fire:
"Shining Star"]

29:21.230 --> 29:23.720
♪ ♪

29:28.510 --> 29:30.710
We didn't even come to this
neighborhood when I was a kid.

29:30.910 --> 29:33.920
Now you bought your mom
a house here.

29:34.120 --> 29:35.340
Oh, Mrs. Dunne.

29:35.540 --> 29:36.840
So good to see you.

29:37.040 --> 29:38.670
Um, this is Lisa.

29:38.870 --> 29:41.010
- Obviously.
- Hi.

29:41.210 --> 29:42.930
I mean, wow, God,

29:43.130 --> 29:44.640
I loved you in that
Gene Wilder movie.

29:44.840 --> 29:47.600
You're so sweet.
Thank you.

29:47.800 --> 29:49.770
And you're with Warren?

29:49.970 --> 29:52.310
[laughs]
Yeah, right?

29:52.510 --> 29:54.480
I'm telling you, it's gonna
make the Stooges

29:54.680 --> 29:55.980
look like the Carpenters.

29:56.180 --> 29:58.150
And, you know,
you got the Ramones,

29:58.350 --> 30:00.400
and all this stuff
coming from London...

30:00.600 --> 30:02.550
[indistinct chatter]

30:03.960 --> 30:06.300
[Eddie] Let's, uh,
let's go this way.

30:09.930 --> 30:14.080
Um, I'm gonna go, uh, go hang
with them for a sec.

30:14.280 --> 30:15.420
Hi, Julia.

30:15.620 --> 30:17.880
Hey, Mama, why don't you let me
and Daisy have

30:18.080 --> 30:20.050
a quick little second alone,
and you can go talk to Daddy.

30:20.250 --> 30:21.510
- He's right there.
- Oh, she's fine.

30:21.710 --> 30:22.630
Oh, no, no, no. She just...

30:22.830 --> 30:24.680
She's a beautiful kid.

30:24.880 --> 30:29.060
Oh, she is obsessed with you.
[laughs]

30:29.260 --> 30:31.310
Every day it's, "I want to look
like Daisy Jones,

30:31.510 --> 30:32.980
I want my hair to look
like Daisy Jones,

30:33.180 --> 30:35.250
and I want to sing
like Daisy Jones."

30:38.250 --> 30:40.990
Do you ever think about it?

30:41.180 --> 30:43.280
About having kids?

30:43.480 --> 30:44.820
- Yeah, having kids.
- No.

30:45.020 --> 30:47.200
- [Daisy laughs]
- Why?

30:47.400 --> 30:48.910
No.

30:49.110 --> 30:52.120
My parents didn't want kids.
My mother especially.

30:52.320 --> 30:54.790
So I went from being
an accident

30:54.990 --> 30:58.090
to an inconvenience
to an afterthought,

30:58.290 --> 31:00.800
and then, I think
the worst thing of all...

31:01.000 --> 31:02.380
Which was what?

31:02.580 --> 31:04.570
Competition.

31:08.530 --> 31:12.270
- But you know, all parents
fuck their kids up.
- That's true.

31:12.470 --> 31:14.980
I don't really want to
be responsible

31:15.180 --> 31:18.230
- for doing that
to somebody else.
- Mm.

31:18.430 --> 31:20.580
And that's why you won't.

31:21.630 --> 31:23.900
Don't count yourself out
this early, Daisy.

31:24.100 --> 31:27.720
You are all sorts of things
you don't even know.

31:30.010 --> 31:32.300
Yeah?

31:33.470 --> 31:34.790
<i>[Eddie] So wait, you go by</i>
<i>"Dr. Loving" now?</i>

31:34.990 --> 31:38.080
DDS. Doctor of Dental Services.

31:38.280 --> 31:40.960
[Warren] ♪ <i>Dr. Lovin'</i> ♪

31:41.160 --> 31:43.130
I love that, man.
It sounds like a skin flick.

31:43.330 --> 31:45.510
[Graham] Well, good on you, man.

31:45.710 --> 31:47.800
- You built a nice life here.
- Yeah, thanks.

31:48.000 --> 31:49.010
Yeah, I mean,
sometimes I think about

31:49.210 --> 31:50.850
if I'd stayed in the band,
but then I think

31:51.050 --> 31:52.720
I got something you guys
will never have:

31:52.920 --> 31:54.930
financial security.

31:55.130 --> 31:57.810
It's not glamorous,
but it's something, you know.

31:58.010 --> 32:00.650
Besides, after taxes
and split six ways,

32:00.850 --> 32:03.330
you guys can't be
making that much, right?

32:06.170 --> 32:08.590
- Let's, uh, let's
get Chuck another beer.
- Yeah.

32:18.140 --> 32:19.500
Oh, what's going on?

32:19.700 --> 32:21.770
No, it's nothing. I'm fine.

32:32.570 --> 32:35.560
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

32:35.760 --> 32:36.680
See, I like this one.

32:36.880 --> 32:37.810
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

32:38.010 --> 32:38.890
That's actually
my favorite, too.

32:39.090 --> 32:42.400
- Hey, what's this?
- Aww.

32:42.600 --> 32:45.610
She was chasing sandpipers
at the beach, and...

32:45.810 --> 32:47.190
she just thought it was
the funniest thing

32:47.390 --> 32:48.650
she'd ever seen
in her whole life.

32:48.850 --> 32:51.200
- Oh, yeah, she looks so happy.
- Yeah.

32:51.400 --> 32:53.870
She's growing up, huh?

32:54.070 --> 32:55.390
Mm.

32:57.390 --> 33:00.370
What would you think

33:00.570 --> 33:04.980
about... maybe trying again?

33:07.860 --> 33:10.050
Not now, obviously,

33:10.250 --> 33:13.610
but maybe after the tour?

33:14.990 --> 33:16.770
I don't know, Julia could...

33:16.970 --> 33:20.190
could definitely use a sibling,
and I just...

33:20.390 --> 33:22.690
feel like we would
be ready this time.

33:22.890 --> 33:25.170
You want to have another baby?

33:27.040 --> 33:29.340
I really do.

33:32.210 --> 33:33.820
- What?
- Okay.

33:34.020 --> 33:35.830
- Was that a yes?
- Mm-hmm.

33:36.030 --> 33:37.200
[laughing]
Well, not now.

33:37.400 --> 33:38.200
We're in your mother's house.

33:38.400 --> 33:39.660
I don't care.

33:39.860 --> 33:42.380
- [Camila laughing]
- [Billy] No, come on.

33:42.570 --> 33:45.380
<i>[Daisy] I remember that night.</i>

33:45.580 --> 33:47.710
It was the first time
in I don't know how long

33:47.910 --> 33:49.300
that I didn't want to
take anything.

33:49.500 --> 33:52.360
I didn't want alcohol,
I didn't want drugs.

33:56.240 --> 33:59.390
I knew exactly
what I wanted.

33:59.590 --> 34:01.730
- [Billy] I can't speak
for all of you...
- [crowd cheering]

34:01.930 --> 34:05.330
...but I sure as hell wouldn't
trade this for anything.

34:06.620 --> 34:08.280
Thank you.

34:08.480 --> 34:09.780
All right, who we
playing for tonight?

34:09.980 --> 34:12.550
For family.
"Pittsburgh" on three.

34:16.130 --> 34:17.660
One, two, three.

34:17.860 --> 34:18.870
[all] Pittsburgh!

34:19.070 --> 34:20.870
[♪ "Regret Me"]

